<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nine" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nine,</orth> one more than eight: <bibl n="shak. son 38.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 38, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.135" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 2, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.488" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 488</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.488" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 488</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.488" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 488</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.63" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.24" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.236" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 236</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.9.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 9, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.169" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.4.8" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 183</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.175" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 175</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.188" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 2, 85</bibl>. <cit><quote>the n. men's morris,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 98</bibl></cit> (see <emph>Morris</emph>). <cit><quote>the n. Worthies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 124</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.238" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 238</bibl>. <cit><quote>the n. sibyls of old Rome,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 56</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I was seven of the n. days out of the wonder,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 184</bibl></cit> (alluding to the proverb: <emph>a wonder lasts but nine days;</emph> cf. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 113</bibl>). Thought to be the usual number of the young of some animals: <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 65</bibl> (in <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 71</bibl> M. Edd. <emph>the youngest wren of n.;</emph> O. Edd. <emph>of mine</emph>). A number of magical power: <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 22</bibl> A cat has nine lives: <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 81</bibl>.
